Heute l√ºften wir das Geheimnis um den Unterschied zwischen Melange und Cappuccino. Der Cappuccino besteht gemeinhin aus einem Espresso und homogen gesch√§umter Milch. Today we shed a little light on the difference between the classic melange and the Italian cappuccino. The cappuccino consists of one shot of espresso combined with homogeneously frothed milk. The melange on the other hand consists of 3 parts: espresso, steamed milk and frothed milk on top. Rumours have it that the original version of the famous coffee drink was made with filtered coffee. One thing is certain, the best companion to a melange is our Demel carrot cake. .
